, about whom virtually nothing factual is known, although a vast body of legend grew up around him, and he became the patron saint of Greece and of Russia, as well as of children, sailors, merchants, and pawnbrokers. His feast day is  6 December , and among the many roles which legend has assigned to him is that of bringer of Christmas presents, in the guise of ‘Santa Claus’ (an alteration of the Dutch form of his name, <i>Sinterklaas</i>)."]},{"name":"Nels","meanings":["vernacular form of   Niklas ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1357055,"age":29,"year":"1617","julianDay":2311658,"description":"Treaty of Stolbovo ended Swedish occupation of Northern Russia.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1357056,"age":30,"year":"1618","julianDay":2312023,"description":"1618-1648 Sweden fights in the Thirty Years' War.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1357057,"age":40,"year":"1628","julianDay":2315675,"description":"Swedish warship Vasa sank in Stockholm harbor. 25 drowned.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1702087,"age":42,"year":"1630","julianDay":2316406,"title":"The Thirty Years' War","description":"King Gustavus Adolphus entered Sweden into the Thirty Years' War in 1630 with great success on the side of the German Protestants.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thirty_Years%27_War","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Thirty Years' War","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1357058,"age":49,"year":"1637","julianDay":2318963,"description":"Swedish immigrants sailed to Delaware.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Cornelius Nils Jestenburgh was born in 1588, in Skänninge, Stockholm, Sweden, his father, Adriaan van Groenewegen, was 18 and his mother, Anna Holschers, was 18. He had at least 1 daughter with Brita Persdotter. He died on 28 January 1652, at the age of 64."},"et":{"1588–28 January 1652":"1588–28. jaanuar 1652","1588–1652":"1588–1652","1590–1663":"1590–1663","1612–1692":"1612–1692","1570–1641":"1570–1641","1570–Female":"1570–Surnud","1692":"1692","1570":"1570","1590":"1590","1612":"1612",